The '''20th [[Chess Olympiad]]''', organized by the [[F<U+00E9>d<U+00E9>ration Internationale des <U+00C9>checs|FIDE]] and comprising an open<ref> Although commonly referred to as the ''men's division'', this section is open to both [[male]] and [[female]] players.</ref> and women's tournament, as well as several events designed to promote the game of [[chess]], took place between September 18 and October 13, 1972, in [[Skopje]], [[Yugoslavia]] (present-day [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]]). 
This Olympiad was the first major success for the [[Benko Gambit]]. In sixteen games, Black players scored ten wins and six [[draw (chess)|draws]] with the [[chess opening|opening]].

